---
title: logs_bloom (osaka-bloom)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_iter_logs : bloom = bytearray(256 zero bytes)
    q_iter_logs --> q_add_addr : has next log
    q_add_addr --> q_iter_topics : add_to_bloom(bloom, log.address)
    q_iter_topics --> q_add_topic : for topic in log.topics
    q_add_topic --> q_iter_topics : add_to_bloom(bloom, topic)
    q_iter_topics --> q_iter_logs : topics exhausted
    q_iter_logs --> q_return : logs exhausted
    q_return --> q_final : return Bloom(bloom)
    q_final --> [*] : done

    note right of q_init
        INV: bloom is initialized to all zeros (256 bytes)
    end note

    note right of q_add_addr
        INV: Every log address is added to the
        bloom filter exactly once
    end note

    note right of q_add_topic
        INV: Every topic of every log is added to
        the bloom filter exactly once
    end note

    note right of q_return
        INV: The returned Bloom is constructed from the
        mutated bytearray after all logs are processed.
        add_to_bloom is called (1 + len(log.topics))
        times per log entry.
    end note
